canonical:
  title: 劉貂讓中大夫判將作監事不允批答
  author: 李奎報
  language: lzh
  text: 云云官局之務各有司存然厥務之或廢由主者之不良朕悶之久矣思得才吏董之况今之將作古之繕工務叢事鉅其任尤重若委之非其人則其何事之有濟耶汝自彈冠於仕路嘗游刃於吏能截劇剸煩多多益辦開物成務綽綽有餘使乎延譽於東南公耳忘勞於夙夜曾貳計司則籌筭若唐之延朗及居選部則品裁如晉之山濤不有異思曷償殊績故除三品之秩得領九工之司當體眷懷毋煩固讓云云
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 劉貂讓中大夫判將作監事不允批答
  author: 李奎報
  language: lzh
  text: 云云。官局之務。各有司存。然厥務之或廢。由主者之不良。朕悶之久矣。思得才吏董之。况今之將作。古之繕工。務叢事鉅。其任尤重。若委之非其人。則其何事之有濟耶。汝自彈冠於仕路。嘗游刃於吏能。截劇剸煩。多多益辦。開物成務。綽綽有餘。使乎延譽於東南。公耳忘勞於夙夜。曾貳計司則籌筭若唐之延朗。及居選部則品裁。如晉之山濤。不有異思。曷償殊績。故除三品之秩。得領九工之司。當體眷懷。毋煩固讓云云。
korean:
  title: 유초 양 중대부 판장작감사 불윤 비답
  author: 이규보
  language: kor
  text: 운운. 관청의 사무는 유사(有司)가 각기 있으나, 사무가 혹 폐기됨은 주무관(主務官)이 못났기 때문이다. 짐이 이를 민망스럽게 여긴 지 오래로, 재능이 있는 관리를 가려 사무를 감독케 하려고 생각하여 왔다. 하물며 지금의 장작(將作)은 옛날의 선공(繕工)으로, 사무가 번잡하고 일이 거창하여 그 책임이 더욱 무겁다. 그러니 적임자에게 맡기지 않으면 무슨 일을 성취할 수 있겠는가.그대는 벼슬길에 나서서부터 늘 관리의 능숙한 재능을 발휘하여, 어렵고 복잡한 일을 처리할 때 일이 많을수록 더 잘 처리하였고, 도리를 알아 실제로 시행함에 있어서 여유작작하였다. 사자(使者)로서 동남쪽 지방으로 가서 명예를 날리었고, 사사로움을 잊고 공을 알아 일찍 일어나고 늦게 자서 수고를 잊었다. 일찍이 주계(主計)의 차관(次官)으로 계산이 당(唐)나라 때의 연랑(延朗)과 같았고, 이부(吏部)에 있어서는 인재를 선발함이 진(晉)나라 때의 산도(山濤)와 같았다. 그러니 각별한 은전이 아니면 어찌 특수한 공적을 갚겠는가. 그러므로 이제 삼품의 계급을 제수하여 구공(九工)의 관서(官署)를 거느리게 하였다. 그러니 마땅히 마음을 잘 받들어 번거로이 사양하지 말라. 운운.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0320_020_0320&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Royal Decree Rejecting Liu Zhao's Petition to Decline the Position of Minister of Public Works
  author: Lee Gyu-bo
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The duties of government offices rest with their respective officials. Yet when these duties fall into neglect, it is because those in charge lack ability. I have long been troubled by this, and have sought capable administrators to oversee such work. How much more so with the Ministry of Public Works—ancient keeper of repairs and construction—whose tasks are manifold and whose burdens are grave. If we entrust this to one unfit for the role, how can anything be accomplished?

    Since first you entered the civil service, you have consistently demonstrated mastery of administrative skill. Complex and arduous matters become tractable under your hand; the more numerous the tasks, the more deftly you manage them. In bringing order to affairs, you move with perfect ease. As emissary to the southeastern regions, you earned renown. Forgetting personal comfort in service to the public, you labored through dawn and dusk without complaint. When you served as deputy minister of the Bureau of Accounts, your calculations rivaled those of Yan Lang of the Tang. When you held office in the Ministry of Personnel, your judgment in selecting talent matched that of Shan Tao of the Jin. Such exceptional virtue cannot be repaid save through exceptional trust. Therefore, I now grant you the rank of the Third Order and appoint you to oversee the Nine Bureaus of Public Works. Receive this mark of favor with a grateful heart. Do not presume to decline again.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: Liu Zhao (劉貂) was a historical official whom Lee Gyu-bo addresses in this royal decree rejecting his petition to decline appointment as Minister of Public Works.
  - key: ''
    value: The Nine Bureaus of Public Works (九工) refers to the nine divisions responsible for various construction and maintenance projects in imperial administration.
  - key: ''
    value: Yan Lang (延朗) of the Tang dynasty was renowned for his skill in mathematical calculation and accounting, serving as a model of administrative excellence.
  - key: ''
    value: Shan Tao (山濤) of the Jin dynasty was celebrated for his discernment in selecting capable officials and identifying talent, representing the ideal merit-based administrator.
